# DarwinKPI

DarwinKPI is a business Key Performance Indicator (KPI) platform for workforce analytics, real-time tracking, and actionable insights.

---

## Table of Contents

- [Features](#features)
- [Project Structure](#project-structure)
- [Getting Started](#getting-started)
  - [Backend Setup](#backend-setup)
  - [Frontend Setup](#frontend-setup)
- [Removing Data from Repository](#removing-data-from-repository)
- [GitHub Remote Setup](#github-remote-setup)
---

## Features

- Real-time KPI tracking
- Comprehensive analytics and reporting
- User management
- Custom dashboards

---

## Project Structure

```
darwinKPI/
│
├── client/      # Angular frontend application
├── server/      # Node.js backend server
├── data/        # Data files (excluded from git)
├── README       # Project documentation
└── .gitignore   # Git ignore rules
```

---

## Getting Started


### Backend Setup

```sh
cd server
node index.js
```

### Frontend Setup

```sh
cd client
ng serve --open
```

Open your browser at [http://localhost:4200](http://localhost:4200).

---

## Removing Data from Repository

To remove the `data` folder from git tracking and update `.gitignore`:

```sh
git rm -r --cached data
git add data
git add .gitignore
git commit -m "Removed data folder from Git tracking and updated .gitignore"
```

To remove all history of the `data` folder:

```sh
git filter-repo --path data --invert-paths
git reflog expire --expire=now --all
git gc --prune=now --aggressive
git push origin main --force
```

---

## GitHub Remote Setup

If the remote is not set:

```sh
git remote add origin https://github.com/Famanias/darwinKPI.git
```

